The Association of Blind People in Kaduna state (ABPK) has called on the State Governor, Mallam Nasir el-Rufai to fulfil his 2015 and 2019 campaign promises to them rather than arresting physically challenged persons in the state. The Public Relation Officer (PRO) of ABPK, Mallam Sadiku Ahmed made the appeal while addressing newsmen in Kaduna on Monday. Ahmed said that some of the physically challenged persons have talents, lamenting that there are no jobs for them hence the reason they resort to begging as a means of survival, appealing that the government should help in providing them with employment or skills acquisition. Ahmed appealed to Governor el-rufai to fulfil the promises he made to them during his 2015 and 2019 elections. Ahmed recalled that Governor el-rufai administration promised to give scholarship to their children and to provide them with shelter, and now he is arresting them, he lamented. He also disclosed that Governor el-rufai government has arrested over 114 blind people in the state. 